<p>The First Mother is part of Hermione's life for the rest of Hermione's life. They become, across the decades, something like family. The First Mother attends Hugo's wedding. She attends Rose's. She holds Hermione's grandchildren when they are born. She is, by then, openly known in a small circle as what she is, though the wider wizarding world has not yet been told the full truth.</p>

<p>The full truth will be told. But not in Hermione's lifetime. The First Mother is patient. She has time. Hermione has given her enough that the rest of the work can proceed without urgency.</p>

<p>CHAPTER 42 — Coda</p>
<p>A short final chapter. Many years later.</p>

<p>Hermione is old. She is in her nineties. She has retired from the Ministry decades ago. She lives in the small house she and Ron bought when the children left home. Ron died three years ago. Hermione carries him now — she has learned, from the First Mother, how to carry, though the carrying for a mortal who carries a mortal is a different thing than the First Mother's carrying. The shape of it is similar. The weight is gentler. Ron is in her in the small ways she still hears him in the kitchen sometimes when she is making tea.</p>

